  "response": "Currently, brain transplants as a complete procedure are not possible. While there have been theoretical discussions and some isolated experiments with animal tissues, a full human brain transplant has never been successfully performed. There are several major challenges:\n\n1. Extreme medical complexity\n2. Inability to reconnect millions of precise neural connections\n3. Risk of tissue rejection\n4. Technical limitations of current medical technology\n5. Ethical and philosophical questions about personal identity\n\nSome related medical procedures exist, such as brain tissue grafts or neural stem cell transplants, but a complete brain transplant remains in the realm of science fiction.",
